      "displayName": "Python Design Pattern Examples",
      "html": "<h2>Python Design Pattern Examples</h2>\n<p>Combine with Python. When pattern selection or design review is in scope, also use the matching generic pattern skill.</p>\n<h3>Example Routing</h3>\n<ul><li>Read <a href=\"../skills/python-design-pattern-examples/references/creational-examples-python.md\">Python Creational Examples</a> for the five creational patterns.</li><li>Read <a href=\"../skills/python-design-pattern-examples/references/structural-examples-python.md\">Python Structural Examples</a> for the seven structural patterns.</li><li>Read <a href=\"../skills/python-design-pattern-examples/references/behavioral-examples-python.md\">Python Behavioral Examples</a> for the eleven behavioral patterns.</li><li>Treat examples as minimal sketches and preserve project typing, packaging, exception, resource, async, and test conventions.</li><li>Prefer functions, protocols, dataclasses, module ownership, generators, and context managers when they express the intent directly.</li></ul>\n<h3>Verification</h3>\n<ul><li>Test observable contracts, mutation boundaries, exceptions, resource cleanup, and supported Python versions.</li></ul>",
      "markdown": "---\nname: python-design-pattern-examples\ndescription: Apply the 23 Gang of Four patterns idiomatically in Python, using functions, protocols, dataclasses, modules, iterators, generators, and context managers without changing the generic pattern intent.\nmetadata:\n  category: stack-and-domain\n---\n\n# Python Design Pattern Examples\n\nCombine with Python. When pattern selection or design review is in scope, also use the matching generic pattern skill.\n\n## Example Routing\n\n- Read [Python Creational Examples](references/creational-examples-python.md) for the five creational patterns.\n- Read [Python Structural Examples](references/structural-examples-python.md) for the seven structural patterns.\n- Read [Python Behavioral Examples](references/behavioral-examples-python.md) for the eleven behavioral patterns.\n- Treat examples as minimal sketches and preserve project typing, packaging, exception, resource, async, and test conventions.\n- Prefer functions, protocols, dataclasses, module ownership, generators, and context managers when they express the intent directly.\n\n## Verification\n\n- Test observable contracts, mutation boundaries, exceptions, resource cleanup, and supported Python versions.\n",
      "name": "python-design-pattern-examples",
      "shortDescription": "Apply the 23 Gang of Four patterns idiomatically in Python, using functions, protocols...",
      "sourcePath": "skills/python-design-pattern-examples/SKILL.md"
